{"title_page": "Wave (Meghan Trainor song)", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Wave\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Meghan Trainor - Wave.png\n| alt        = \n| artist     = [[Meghan Trainor]] featuring Mike Sabath\n| album      = [[Treat Myself]]\n| released   = {{start date|2019|9|27}}\n| recorded   = March 5, 2019\n| format     =\n*[[Music download|Digital download]]\n*[[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Electropop]]|[[House music|house]]}} <!-- Sourced in the \"Critical reception\" section -->\n| length     = {{duration|m=2|s=56}}\n| label      = [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n| writer     =\n*Meghan Trainor\n*Mike Sabath\n| producer   = Mike Sabath\n| chronology = [[Meghan Trainor]]\n| prev_title = [[With You (Kaskade and Meghan Trainor song)|With You]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[Nice to Meet Ya (Meghan Trainor song)|Nice to Meet Ya]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|UIevTTLB_3Q|\"Wave\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Wave'''\" is a song recorded by American singer-songwriter [[Meghan Trainor]], featuring producer Mike Sabath, for her third major-label studio album ''[[Treat Myself]]'' (2020). It was written and produced by the duo. The track was released on September 27, 2019, as the second single from the album. Backed by panoramic piano and ostentatious background vocals, the [[electropop]] song lyrically tells the story of the emotional fallout of a failed relationship. The song received mixed reviews from critics. Commercially, it charted at number 35 on the New Zealand Hot Singles chart. [[Mathew Cullen]] directed the [[music video]] for \"Wave\", which features an earthy color palette and Trainor dancing atop a group of people that rock around her like waves. Trainor has performed the song on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' and ''[[The Voice (American TV series)|The Voice]]''.\n\n==Background==\n[[Meghan Trainor]] delayed her August 2018-scheduled third major-label studio album, ''[[Treat Myself]]'', to January 25, 2019, because she wanted to add more songs to it, and removed it from iTunes that month.<ref>{{cite web |last=Nied |first=Mike |title=Change Of Plans: Meghan Trainor Announces 'The Love Train' EP |url=https://www.idolator.com/7694567/meghan-trainor-announces-the-love-train-ep |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=February 4, 2019|accessdate=April 14, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190205122510/http://www.idolator.com/7694567/meghan-trainor-announces-the-love-train-ep |archivedate=February 5, 2019 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Trainor had written \"Wave\" in 2016, and held onto it until 2019. She approached Mike Sabath to produce the song. As the two became close while working on it in the studio, Trainor asked him to record a verse for the song. Sabath stated that he was \"super inspired\" by her voice and the energy of the people in the studio, and finished his verse in one take and filled in the lyrics.<ref name=\"PulledIn\" /> It was recorded on March 5, 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet|author=[[Meghan Trainor|Trainor, Meghan]]|user=Meghan_Trainor|number=1213148307733696512|title=The day we recorded #Wave 2019 blessed me with my new buddy @MikeSabathMusic|date=January 3, 2020|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref> Sabath went on to produce five of the fifteen tracks from the album, co-writing four of them.<ref name=\"Notes\" >{{cite AV media notes |title=[[Treat Myself]] |others=Meghan Trainor |publisher=[[Epic Records]]}}</ref>\n\nTrainor announced the release date along with the single artwork for \"Wave\" on September 25, 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet|author=Trainor, Meghan|user=Meghan_Trainor|number=1176891405920276482|title=#Wave Featuring @MikeSabathMusic coming Friday|date=September 25, 2019|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref> The song was [[Music download|digitally]] released two days later, as the second single from ''Treat Myself''.<ref name=\"ITV\" /> On October 7, 2019, a solo version of it was serviced to [[hot adult contemporary]] radio stations in the United States.<ref name=\"AA\" /> A Remix EP to promote \"Wave\" was released on November 22, 2019, featuring remixes of the song by [[R3hab]], [[Justin Caruso]] and Arkadi.<ref name=\"Remixes\" >{{cite web | url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/wave-feat-mike-sabath-single/1488412692 | title=Wave (feat. Mike Sabath) - Single by Meghan Trainor | publisher=[[Apple Music]] | accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\nAbout the inspiration for \"Wave\", Trainor said that \"there was this guy that was -- this poor dude, I'm probably talkin' 'bout him everywhere. But he was like, 'We can't ever be together 'cause it won't last!' But he'd be like, 'I love you' and I was like 'Ok, why are you calling then? Like why is this a thing?' So I don't know how to express myself with words, so I wrote this song and I sent it to him\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Rowley |first=Glenn |title=Meghan Trainor Reveals Lizzo's Surprising Connection to Her Song 'Me Too' |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8532039/meghan-trainor-lilly-singh-interview-lizzo |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 3, 2019}}</ref> She has stated that she has \"never worked harder on a song\" and that Sabath took it to a whole new level.<ref name=\"PulledIn\" />\n\n==Composition==\nAn [[electropop]] song,<ref name=\"Idolator\" /> \"Wave\" begins with Trainor delivering titanic vocals over a panoramic piano instrumentation, which transitions into an [[electronic dance music]] pulse that was compared to the work of [[Cascada]]. The song features \"ostentatious\" background vocals with gospel-inflected harmonies that she stated were inspired by her visits to [[Kanye West]]'s [[Sunday Service Choir]] shows.<ref name=\"Pitchfork\" >{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/meghan-trainor-treat-myself/|title=Meghan Trainor: Treat Myself Album Review|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Blum|first=Dani|date=February 6, 2020|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref> Described as a \"frothy electro-bop\", its lyrics detail the highs and lows of a dramatic love story.<ref name=\"Idolate\">{{cite web |last=Nied |first=Mike |title=Album Review: Meghan Trainor's 'Treat Myself' Was Worth The Wait |url=https://www.idolator.com/7906273/album-review-meghan-trainors-treat-myself-was-worth-the-wait |website=Idolator |accessdate=April 17, 2020 |date=February 3, 2020}}</ref> \"Wave\" talks about the emotional fallout of a relationship that has failed, with lyrics like \"And I shouldn't beg for more/But I don't want it to end\".<ref name=\"Rolling\" /> It has been called a drastic departure from Trainor's traditional [[doo-wop]] sound by ''[[PopMatters]]''{{'}} Jessica Brant.<ref name=\"PMatters\" >{{cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/meghan-trainor-treat-myself-review-2644975044.html|title=Meghan Trainor: Treat Myself (album review)|website=[[PopMatters]]|last=Brant|first=Jessica|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe song received mixed reviews from critics. ''[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'''s Mike Nied wrote that \"Wave\" finds \"the duo [riding] the waves of their love story\", adding that \"the end result feels more mature and graceful than some of Meghan's more saccharine bops\" and that he loved the creative direction.<ref name=\"Idolator\" >{{cite web |last=Nied |first=Mike |title=Meghan Trainor & Mike Sabath's 'Wave' Is Electro-Pop Perfection |url=http://www.idolator.com/7889167/meghan-trainor-mike-sabaths-wave-is-electro-pop-perfection |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> Nied stated that it may very well be Trainor's best song yet, and is the \"sort of mature anthem that could very easily take her career to another level\".<ref name=\"Idolate\" /> Heran Mamo of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' opined that \"the backing choir adds an ethereal layer over the electronic impressions\" on \"Wave\", and that \"the chorus is a powerfully sweeping recital that emphasizes just how overwhelming her desire to get this love back is\".<ref name=\"PulledIn\" >{{cite web |last=Mamo |first=Heran |title=Meghan Trainor Gets Pulled In by a 'Wave' of Emotions in New Single, Feat. Mike Sabath |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8531609/meghan-trainor-wave-mike-sabath-listen |website=Billboard |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Entertainment Tonight Canada]]'', Corey Atad described it as \"anthemic and danceable\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Atad |first=Corey |title=Meghan Trainor Debuts Anthemic New Single 'Wave' Featuring Mike Sabath |url=https://etcanada.com/news/514120/meghan-trainor-debuts-anthemic-new-single-wave-featuring-mike-sabath/ |website=[[Entertainment Tonight Canada]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref> In a negative review, Hannah Mylrea of ''[[NME]]'' stated that the song \"starts slow before erupting into a tacky [[House music|house]] mess that would sound at home soundtracking ''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mylrea |first1=Hannah |title=Meghan Trainor - 'Treat Myself' review: pure 'High School Musical' (without the fun basketball scenes) |url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/meghan-trainor-treat-myself-review-2603850 |website=[[NME]] |accessdate=February 27, 2020 |date=February 3, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''{{'}}s Dani Blum called it \"a Cascada remix for a middle school dance in a sweaty gym\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork\" />\n\n==Music video==\nDirected by [[Mathew Cullen]] and choreographed by Charm La'Donna, the music video for \"Wave\" was released on October 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Williams |first=Cat |title=Meghan Trainor Gets Swept Up By A Crowd In Her New Video For 'Wave' Featuring Mike Sabath |url=https://etcanada.com/news/519170/meghan-trainor-gets-swept-up-by-a-crowd-in-her-new-video-for-wave-featuring-mike-sabath/ |website=Entertainment Tonight Canada |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> It features an earthy color palette and depicts Trainor in an abstract dance party where she glides above the hands of several people.<ref>{{cite web |last=Fields |first=Taylor |title=Meghan Trainor Takes Fans Behind The Scenes of Her 'Wave' Music Video |url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-10-04-meghan-trainor-takes-fans-behind-the-scenes-of-her-wave-music-video/ |website=[[iHeartRadio]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> Trainor, who is clad in a nude-colored leotard, dances atop a group of people that rock back and forth. They catch and release her body in rhythm with quivering synths, so as to simulate a human wave.<ref name=\"PMatters\" /> The dancers are dressed in neutral tones and form a giant pyramid shape.<ref>{{cite web |title=Meghan Trainor Rises Above The Pack in 'Wave' Video |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8532354/meghan-trainor-wave-video |website=Billboard |accessdate=April 17, 2020 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> The dancers crash like waves around Trainor, as if she were a rock in the water.<ref name=\"MTV\" >{{cite web |last=Roth |first=Madeline |title=Meghan Trainor Rides A Sea Of Bodies In Ethereal 'Wave' Video |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3141504/meghan-trainor-wave-video/ |publisher=[[MTV News]] |accessdate=April 17, 2020 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> Sabath joins in later, donning a leopard print headband.<ref name=\"Rolling\" >{{cite web |last=Shaffer |first=Claire |title=Meghan Trainor Rides a Tsunami of People in 'Wave' Video |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/meghan-trainor-mike-sabath-wave-video-895695/ |website=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe music video received positive reviews from critics. ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'}}s Claire Shaffer wrote that abstract dance party in the video \"transform[s] into an almost spiritual experience for Trainor\".<ref name=\"Rolling\" /> Writing for [[MTV News]], Madeline Roth described the choreography as \"pristine\", adding that the singer looked \"absolutely ethereal in a tulle gown\".<ref name=\"MTV\" /> Jessica Brant of ''PopMatters'' was positive of the video, stating that the dance moves were executed with \"short, military precision\" and elaborated that the visuals see Trainor \"evocatively stage a physical representation of the enduring power of a shipwrecked romance shared between two partners\".<ref name=\"PMatters\" />\n\n==Live performances==\nTrainor and Sabath performed \"Wave\" for the first time, on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', on November 6, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sawant |first=Drushti |title=Meghan Trainor Introduces Mike Sabath And Performs On The Ellen Show |url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/hollywood-news/meghan-trainor-introduces-mike-sabath-and-performs-on-the-ellen-show.html |publisher=[[Republic TV]] |accessdate=April 15, 2020 |date=November 11, 2019}}</ref> They also performed the song at ''[[The Voice (American TV series)|The Voice]]'' on December 3, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Aniftos |first=Rania |title=Meghan Trainor, Kane Brown, John Legend & Kelly Clarkson to Perform on 'The Voice' |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8545032/meghan-trainor-kane-brown-john-legend-kelly-clarkson-the-voice |website=Billboard |accessdate=April 15, 2020 |date=November 29, 2019}}</ref> Trainor performed a stripped-back version of it during her ''Billboard'' Live At-Home concert on April 10, 2020, which aimed to raise money for [[Feeding America]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Aniftos |first=Rania |title=Meghan Trainor Covers Britney Spears' 'Lucky' on Ukulele During Billboard Live At-Home Concert |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9356307/meghan-trainor-billboard-live-at-home-concert |website=Billboard |accessdate=April 15, 2020 |date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n* '''Album version'''<ref name=\"Notes\" />\n# \"Wave\" (featuring Mike Sabath) \u2013 2:56\n\n*'''Remix EP'''<ref name=\"Remixes\" />\n# \"Wave\" (featuring Mike Sabath) - [[R3hab]] Remix \u2013 3:13\n# \"Wave\" (featuring Mike Sabath) - [[Justin Caruso]] Remix \u2013 4:04\n# \"Wave\" (featuring Mike Sabath) - Arkadi Remix \u2013 3:35\n\n== Personnel ==\nCredits adapted from the album liner notes, ''[[Treat Myself]]'' (2020).<ref name=\"Notes\" />\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* Meghan Trainor \u2013 lead vocals, background vocals, synthesizer\n* Mike Sabath \u2013 [[Record producer|producer]], featured vocals, bass, drums, recording engineer, synthesizer\n* Randy Merrill \u2013 mastering engineer\n* Serban Ghenea \u2013 mixing engineer\n{{col-2}}\n* Camila Viola \u2013 background vocals\n* [[Daryl Sabara]] \u2013 background vocals\n* Jordan Federman \u2013 background vocals\n* Ryan Trainor \u2013 background vocals\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Hot Singles ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/chart/hotsingles?chart=4757|title=NZ Hot Singles Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=October 7, 2019|accessdate=October 7, 2019}}</ref>\n| 35\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Version\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| {{abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| September 27, 2019\n| {{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| Original\n| rowspan=3|[[Epic Records|Epic]]\n| <ref name=\"ITV\" >{{cite web |last=Collins |first=Susan |title=Multi-platinum selling, Grammy\u00ae Award-winning singer-songwriter Meghan Trainor joins the superstar Coaching panel on the new series of ITV's The Voice UK |url=https://www.itv.com/presscentre/press-releases/multi-platinum-selling-grammyr-award-winning-singer-songwriter-meghan-trainor-joins |website=[[ITV News]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| United States\n| October 7, 2019\n| [[Hot adult contemporary]]\n| Solo\n| <ref name=\"AA\" >{{cite web |title=Hot/Modern/AC Future Releases \u2013 Hot Adult Contemporary Rock Songs and Release Dates |url=https://www.allaccess.com/hot-modern-ac/future-releases |work=AllAccess |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191006225320/https://www.allaccess.com/hot-modern-ac/future-releases |archivedate=October 6, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Various\n| November 22, 2019\n| {{hlist|Digital download|streaming}}\n| Remixes\n| <ref name=\"Remixes\" />\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Meghan Trainor}}\n\n[[Category:2019 singles]]\n[[Category:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:Epic Records singles]]\n[[Category:Meghan Trainor songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Meghan Trainor]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mike Sabath]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = Wave\n| type       = single\n| cover      = Meghan Trainor - Wave.png\n| alt        = \n| artist     = [[Meghan Trainor]] featuring Mike Sabath\n| album      = [[Treat Myself]]\n| released   = {{start date|2019|9|27}}\n| recorded   = March 5, 2019\n| format     =\n*[[Music download|Digital download]]\n*[[Streaming media|streaming]]\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Electropop]]|[[House music|house]]}} <!-- Sourced in the \"Critical reception\" section -->\n| length     = {{duration|m=2|s=56}}\n| label      = [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n| writer     =\n*Meghan Trainor\n*Mike Sabath\n| producer   = Mike Sabath\n| chronology = [[Meghan Trainor]]\n| prev_title = [[With You (Kaskade and Meghan Trainor song)|With You]]\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = [[Nice to Meet Ya (Meghan Trainor song)|Nice to Meet Ya]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{External music video|{{YouTube|UIevTTLB_3Q|\"Wave\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Wave'''\" is a song recorded by American singer-songwriter [[Meghan Trainor]], featuring producer Mike Sabath, for her third major-label studio album ''[[Treat Myself]]'' (2020). It was written and produced by the duo. The track was released on September 27, 2019, as the second single from the album. Backed by panoramic piano and ostentatious background vocals, the [[electropop]] song lyrically tells the story of the emotional fallout of a failed relationship. The song received mixed reviews from critics. Commercially, it charted at number 35 on the New Zealand Hot Singles chart. [[Mathew Cullen]] directed the [[music video]] for \"Wave\", which features an earthy color palette and Trainor dancing atop a group of people that rock around her like waves. Trainor has performed the song on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' and ''[[The Voice (American TV series)|The Voice]]''.\n\n==Background==\n[[Meghan Trainor]] delayed her August 2018-scheduled third major-label studio album, ''[[Treat Myself]]'', to January 25, 2019, because she wanted to add more songs to it, and removed it from iTunes that month.<ref>{{cite web |last=Nied |first=Mike |title=Change Of Plans: Meghan Trainor Announces 'The Love Train' EP |url=https://www.idolator.com/7694567/meghan-trainor-announces-the-love-train-ep |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=February 4, 2019|accessdate=April 14, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190205122510/http://www.idolator.com/7694567/meghan-trainor-announces-the-love-train-ep |archivedate=February 5, 2019 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Trainor had written \"Wave\" in 2016, and held onto it until 2019. She approached Mike Sabath to produce the song. As the two became close while working on it in the studio, Trainor asked him to record a verse for the song. Sabath stated that he was \"super inspired\" by her voice and the energy of the people in the studio, and finished his verse in one take and filled in the lyrics.<ref name=\"PulledIn\" /> It was recorded on March 5, 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet|author=[[Meghan Trainor|Trainor, Meghan]]|user=Meghan_Trainor|number=1213148307733696512|title=The day we recorded #Wave 2019 blessed me with my new buddy @MikeSabathMusic|date=January 3, 2020|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref> Sabath went on to produce five of the fifteen tracks from the album, co-writing four of them.<ref name=\"Notes\" >{{cite AV media notes |title=[[Treat Myself]] |others=Meghan Trainor |publisher=[[Epic Records]]}}</ref>\n\nTrainor announced the release date along with the single artwork for \"Wave\" on September 25, 2019.<ref>{{cite tweet|author=Trainor, Meghan|user=Meghan_Trainor|number=1176891405920276482|title=#Wave Featuring @MikeSabathMusic coming Friday|date=September 25, 2019|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref> The song was [[Music download|digitally]] released two days later, as the second single from ''Treat Myself''.<ref name=\"ITV\" /> On October 7, 2019, a solo version of it was serviced to [[hot adult contemporary]] radio stations in the United States.<ref name=\"AA\" /> A Remix EP to promote \"Wave\" was released on November 22, 2019, featuring remixes of the song by [[R3hab]], [[Justin Caruso]] and Arkadi.<ref name=\"Remixes\" >{{cite web | url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/wave-feat-mike-sabath-single/1488412692 | title=Wave (feat. Mike Sabath) - Single by Meghan Trainor | publisher=[[Apple Music]] | accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\nAbout the inspiration for \"Wave\", Trainor said that \"there was this guy that was -- this poor dude, I'm probably talkin' 'bout him everywhere. But he was like, 'We can't ever be together 'cause it won't last!' But he'd be like, 'I love you' and I was like 'Ok, why are you calling then? Like why is this a thing?' So I don't know how to express myself with words, so I wrote this song and I sent it to him\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Rowley |first=Glenn |title=Meghan Trainor Reveals Lizzo's Surprising Connection to Her Song 'Me Too' |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8532039/meghan-trainor-lilly-singh-interview-lizzo |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 3, 2019}}</ref> She has stated that she has \"never worked harder on a song\" and that Sabath took it to a whole new level.<ref name=\"PulledIn\" />\n\n==Composition==\nAn [[electropop]] song,<ref name=\"Idolator\" /> \"Wave\" begins with Trainor delivering titanic vocals over a panoramic piano instrumentation, which transitions into an [[electronic dance music]] pulse that was compared to the work of [[Cascada]]. The song features \"ostentatious\" background vocals with gospel-inflected harmonies that she stated were inspired by her visits to [[Kanye West]]'s [[Sunday Service Choir]] shows.<ref name=\"Pitchfork\" >{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/meghan-trainor-treat-myself/|title=Meghan Trainor: Treat Myself Album Review|website=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|last=Blum|first=Dani|date=February 6, 2020|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref> Described as a \"frothy electro-bop\", its lyrics detail the highs and lows of a dramatic love story.<ref name=\"Idolate\">{{cite web |last=Nied |first=Mike |title=Album Review: Meghan Trainor's 'Treat Myself' Was Worth The Wait |url=https://www.idolator.com/7906273/album-review-meghan-trainors-treat-myself-was-worth-the-wait |website=Idolator |accessdate=April 17, 2020 |date=February 3, 2020}}</ref> \"Wave\" talks about the emotional fallout of a relationship that has failed, with lyrics like \"And I shouldn't beg for more/But I don't want it to end\".<ref name=\"Rolling\" /> It has been called a drastic departure from Trainor's traditional [[doo-wop]] sound by ''[[PopMatters]]''{{'}} Jessica Brant.<ref name=\"PMatters\" >{{cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/meghan-trainor-treat-myself-review-2644975044.html|title=Meghan Trainor: Treat Myself (album review)|website=[[PopMatters]]|last=Brant|first=Jessica|date=January 31, 2020|accessdate=April 17, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nThe song received mixed reviews from critics. ''[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]'''s Mike Nied wrote that \"Wave\" finds \"the duo [riding] the waves of their love story\", adding that \"the end result feels more mature and graceful than some of Meghan's more saccharine bops\" and that he loved the creative direction.<ref name=\"Idolator\" >{{cite web |last=Nied |first=Mike |title=Meghan Trainor & Mike Sabath's 'Wave' Is Electro-Pop Perfection |url=http://www.idolator.com/7889167/meghan-trainor-mike-sabaths-wave-is-electro-pop-perfection |website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> Nied stated that it may very well be Trainor's best song yet, and is the \"sort of mature anthem that could very easily take her career to another level\".<ref name=\"Idolate\" /> Heran Mamo of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' opined that \"the backing choir adds an ethereal layer over the electronic impressions\" on \"Wave\", and that \"the chorus is a powerfully sweeping recital that emphasizes just how overwhelming her desire to get this love back is\".<ref name=\"PulledIn\" >{{cite web |last=Mamo |first=Heran |title=Meghan Trainor Gets Pulled In by a 'Wave' of Emotions in New Single, Feat. Mike Sabath |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8531609/meghan-trainor-wave-mike-sabath-listen |website=Billboard |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref> Writing for ''[[Entertainment Tonight Canada]]'', Corey Atad described it as \"anthemic and danceable\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Atad |first=Corey |title=Meghan Trainor Debuts Anthemic New Single 'Wave' Featuring Mike Sabath |url=https://etcanada.com/news/514120/meghan-trainor-debuts-anthemic-new-single-wave-featuring-mike-sabath/ |website=[[Entertainment Tonight Canada]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref> In a negative review, Hannah Mylrea of ''[[NME]]'' stated that the song \"starts slow before erupting into a tacky [[House music|house]] mess that would sound at home soundtracking ''[[Love Island (2015 TV series)|Love Island]]''.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mylrea |first1=Hannah |title=Meghan Trainor - 'Treat Myself' review: pure 'High School Musical' (without the fun basketball scenes) |url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/meghan-trainor-treat-myself-review-2603850 |website=[[NME]] |accessdate=February 27, 2020 |date=February 3, 2020}}</ref> ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''{{'}}s Dani Blum called it \"a Cascada remix for a middle school dance in a sweaty gym\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork\" />\n\n==Music video==\nDirected by [[Mathew Cullen]] and choreographed by Charm La'Donna, the music video for \"Wave\" was released on October 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Williams |first=Cat |title=Meghan Trainor Gets Swept Up By A Crowd In Her New Video For 'Wave' Featuring Mike Sabath |url=https://etcanada.com/news/519170/meghan-trainor-gets-swept-up-by-a-crowd-in-her-new-video-for-wave-featuring-mike-sabath/ |website=Entertainment Tonight Canada |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> It features an earthy color palette and depicts Trainor in an abstract dance party where she glides above the hands of several people.<ref>{{cite web |last=Fields |first=Taylor |title=Meghan Trainor Takes Fans Behind The Scenes of Her 'Wave' Music Video |url=https://www.iheart.com/content/2019-10-04-meghan-trainor-takes-fans-behind-the-scenes-of-her-wave-music-video/ |website=[[iHeartRadio]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> Trainor, who is clad in a a nude-colored leotard, dances atop a group of people that rock back and forth. They catch and release her body in rhythm with quivering synths, so as to simulate a human wave.<ref name=\"PMatters\" /> The dancers are dressed in neutral tones and form a giant pyramid shape.<ref>{{cite web |title=Meghan Trainor Rises Above The Pack in 'Wave' Video |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8532354/meghan-trainor-wave-video |website=Billboard |accessdate=April 17, 2020 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> The dancers crash like waves around Trainor, as if she were a rock in the water.<ref name=\"MTV\" >{{cite web |last=Roth |first=Madeline |title=Meghan Trainor Rides A Sea Of Bodies In Ethereal 'Wave' Video |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3141504/meghan-trainor-wave-video/ |publisher=[[MTV News]] |accessdate=April 17, 2020 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref> Sabath joins in later, donning a leopard print headband.<ref name=\"Rolling\" >{{cite web |last=Shaffer |first=Claire |title=Meghan Trainor Rides a Tsunami of People in 'Wave' Video |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/meghan-trainor-mike-sabath-wave-video-895695/ |website=[[Rolling Stone]] |accessdate=October 7, 2019 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe music video received positive reviews from critics. ''[[Rolling Stone]]''{{'}}s Claire Shaffer wrote that abstract dance party in the video \"transform[s] into an almost spiritual experience for Trainor\".<ref name=\"Rolling\" /> Writing for [[MTV News]], Madeline Roth described the choreography as \"pristine\", adding that the singer looked \"absolutely ethereal in a tulle gown\".<ref name=\"MTV\" /> Jessica Brant of ''PopMatters'' was positive of the video, stating that the dance moves were executed with \"short, military precision\" and elaborated that the visuals see Trainor \"evocatively stage a physical representation of the enduring power of a shipwrecked romance shared between two partners\".<ref name=\"PMatters\" />\n\n==Live performances==\nTrainor and Sabath performed \"Wave\" for the first time, on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'', on November 6, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sawant |first=Drushti |title=Meghan Trainor Introduces Mike Sabath And Performs On The Ellen Show |url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/hollywood-news/meghan-trainor-introduces-mike-sabath-and-performs-on-the-ellen-show.html |publisher=[[Republic TV]] |accessdate=April 15, 2020 |date=November 11, 2019}}</ref> They also performed the song at ''[[The Voice (American TV series)|The Voice]]'' on December 3, 2019.<ref>{{cite web |last=Aniftos |first=Rania |title=Meghan Trainor, Kane Brown, John Legend & Kelly Clarkson to Perform on 'The Voice' |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8545032/meghan-trainor-kane-brown-john-legend-kelly-clarkson-the-voice |website=Billboard |accessdate=April 15, 2020 |date=November 29, 2019}}</ref> Trainor performed a stripped-back version of it during her ''Billboard'' Live At-Home concert on April 10, 2020, which aimed to raise money for [[Feeding America]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Aniftos |first=Rania |title=Meghan Trainor Covers Britney Spears' 'Lucky' on Ukulele During Billboard Live At-Home Concert |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/9356307/meghan-trainor-billboard-live-at-home-concert |website=Billboard |accessdate=April 15, 2020 |date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n* '''Album version'''<ref name=\"Notes\" />\n# \"Wave\" (featuring Mike Sabath) \u2013 2:56\n\n*'''Remix EP'''<ref name=\"Remixes\" />\n# \"Wave\" (featuring Mike Sabath) - [[R3hab]] Remix \u2013 3:13\n# \"Wave\" (featuring Mike Sabath) - [[Justin Caruso]] Remix \u2013 4:04\n# \"Wave\" (featuring Mike Sabath) - Arkadi Remix \u2013 3:35\n\n== Personnel ==\nCredits adapted from the album liner notes, ''[[Treat Myself]]'' (2020).<ref name=\"Notes\" />\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n* Meghan Trainor \u2013 lead vocals, background vocals, synthesizer\n* Mike Sabath \u2013 [[Record producer|producer]], featured vocals, bass, drums, recording engineer, synthesizer\n* Randy Merrill \u2013 mastering engineer\n* Serban Ghenea \u2013 mixing engineer\n{{col-2}}\n* Camila Viola \u2013 background vocals\n* [[Daryl Sabara]] \u2013 background vocals\n* Jordan Federman \u2013 background vocals\n* Ryan Trainor \u2013 background vocals