:2019 songs]]\n[[Category:Epic Records singles]]\n[[Category:Meghan Trainor songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Meghan Trainor]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Mike Sabath]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word removed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wave_(Meghan_Trainor_song)"}
{"title_page": "Tha Supreme", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian rapper (b. 2001)}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Tha Supreme\n| background       = solo_singer\n| birth_name       = Davide Mattei\n| birth_date       = 17 March 2001\n| birth_place      = Serravalle\n| genre            = Trap music, Hip hop\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n*Rapper\n*Singer\n*Songwriter\n*Record producer}}\n| label            = Epic\n}}\n'''Davide Mattei''' (born 17 March 2001), known by his stage name '''Tha Supreme''', is an Italian rapper, singer and producer from [[Fiumicino]].\n\nHis first mainstream success was thanks to the single \"Perdonami\" by the Italian rapper [[Salmo (rapper)|Salmo]], which he produced.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://notiziemusica.it/chi-e-tha-supreme/curiosita/|title=Chi \u00e8 Tha Supreme, astro nascente dell'hip hop europeo|date=2019-10-23|website=Notizie Musica|language=it-IT|access-date=2019-11-14}}</ref> Following the success of \"Perdonami\", Tha Supreme continued releasing songs of his own and producing for other artists such as [[Marracash]], [[Gemitaiz]] and [[Madman]], [[Izi (rapper)|Izi]] as well as his sister, Sara Mattei.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newsic.it/video-mara-sattei-nuova-registrazione-402-prod-tha-supreme/|title=Video: MARA SATTEI - Nuova Registrazione 402 (prod. tha Supreme)|date=November 13, 2019|language=it}}</ref> His debut album ''23 6451 (in italian it means \"Le basi\", in english \"The basics\")'' was released on 15 November 2019, collecting over 13 million streams in 24 hours.<ref>{{cite web|title=23 6451 by tha Supreme|url=https://music.apple.com/us/album/23-6451/1483480391|website=[[Apple Music]]|access-date=2019-11-15}}</ref>\n\nHe has featured on two Italian number-one singles: \"Yoshi\" with Machete and \"SUPREME - L'ego\" by [[Marracash]] and [[Sfera Ebbasta]].<ref name=\"Italiancharts\"/>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Albums ===\n* ''23 6451'' (2019)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rtl.it/musica/tha-supreme/blun7-a-swishland/|title=Tha Supreme - Blun7 a swishland - RTL 102.5|website=rtl.it|language=it}}</ref> \u2013 No. 1 Italy,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fimi.it/top-of-the-music/classifiche.kl#/charts/1/2019/47|title=Album \u2013 Classifica settimanale WK 47 (dal 15.11.2019 al 21.11.2019)|publisher=[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana]]|language=Italian|accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref> No. 32 Switzerland<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hitparade.ch/album/Tha-Supreme/23-6451-395154|title=Tha Supreme \u2013 23 6451|website=hitparade.ch|accessdate=27 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Singles ===\n\n==== As lead artist ====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles as lead artist, showing year released and album\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:19em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:1em;\"| Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"| Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana|ITA]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fimi.it/top-of-the-music/classifiche.kl#/charts/3/2019/47|title=Top Singoli \u2013 Classifica settimanale WK 47|publisher=[[Federazione Industria Musicale Italiana]]|language=Italian|accessdate=23 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"6itch\"\n| 2017\n| 16\n| {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"5olo\"\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2018\n| 36\n| rowspan=\"5\"| ''23 6451''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"scuol4\"\n| 20\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"oh 9od\"<br><span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(featuring [[Nayt]])</span>\n| 27\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"m8nstar\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n| 17\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"blun7 a swishland\"\n| 1\n|}\n\n==== As featured artist ====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles as featured artist, showing year released, select chart positions and album\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\"